title: Cyclone Alfred a 'practice run' for south-east Queensland buildings, report finds
description: A new report from James Cook University has found aspects of buildings in south-east Queensland and northern New South Wales would become vulnerable to winds only slightly higher than those experienced during ex-Tropical Cyclone Alfred earlier this year.
content: A new report has found buildings in south-east Queensland and northern New South Waleswould only be able to safely withstand weather slightly more severe than what was experienced during ex-Tropical … [+4551 chars]
de: Laut Bericht ist Zyklon Alfred ein „Übungslauf“ für Gebäude im Südosten von Queensland. Ein neuer Bericht der James Cook University hat festgestellt, dass Teile von Gebäuden im Südosten von Queensland und im Norden von New South Wales anfällig für Winde sind, die nur geringfügig stärker sind als während des ehemaligen tropischen Wirbelsturms Alfred Anfang des Jahres.
en: Cyclone Alfred a 'practice run' for south-east Queensland buildings, report finds. A new report from James Cook University has found aspects of buildings in south-east Queensland and northern New South Wales would become vulnerable to winds only slightly higher than those experienced during ex-Tropical Cyclone Alfred earlier this year.
la: Cyclone Alfred "usus currit" pro aedificiis Reginensis meridiano-orientis famam invenit. Nova relatio a James Cook University species aedificiorum in Australia australi-orientis et in septentrionali Nova Wallia Australi-Walliae vulnerabiles ventos paulo altiores fient quam experti ante hoc anno in Cyclone ex-tropico Alfredi.
